-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-BlackBerry, NVIDIA
-- 
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 02:19AM EDT
-- None



June 23 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including AMD, BlackBerry and Nvidia, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * BlackBerry <BBRY.O>: Evercore ups to equal-weight from underweight rating * Kennedy-Wilson <KW.N>: Deutsche Bank starts with buy rating * NVIDIA <NVDA.O>: Pacific Crest cuts to underperform rating   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * AMD <AMD.N>: Pacific Crest cuts to underperform rating * BlackBerry <BBRY.O>: Evercore ups to equal-weight from underweight; target to $10 from $6  * Cubist Pharmaceuticals <CBST.O>: Jefferies raises price target to $88 from $87; rating buy * IFF <IFF.N>: Stifel raises target price to $110 from $103; rating buy * Invensense <INVN.N>: Pacific Crest raises target price to $26 from $22; rating outperform * Kennedy-Wilson <KW.N>: Deutsche Bank starts with buy; $32 target price  * LDR Holding <LDRH.O>: RBC starts with outperform; price target $34  * NVIDIA <NVDA.O>: Pacific Crest cuts to underperform rating * NXP Semiconductors <NXPI.O>: Pacific Crest raises target price to $80 from $72; outperform